This article is a fact sheet released by the White House Office of the Press Secretary in 2014. It highlights the United States' commitment to the collective defense of NATO allies and outlines the efforts made to support NATO allies and partners in response to Russia's aggressive actions. The measures taken include the deployment of additional U.S. aircraft for the Baltic Air Policing mission, enhancing NATO military plans and defense capabilities, and increasing readiness and exercising of the NATO Response Force. The article also mentions specific efforts undertaken by the United States, such as training rotations in Poland, Open Skies Treaty flights over Ukraine, and humanitarian assistance planning. It further provides information on ongoing measures, such as the U.S. force presence in Europe, contributions to the NATO Response Force, and participation in exercises and missile defense initiatives. The article concludes by mentioning NATO meetings and consultations, support to Ukraine, and the suspension of NATO-Russia Council activities.